## 3. `select-name` violations

**None detected.** The `<select id="late-penalty-select">` has a `title` attribute which gives it a programmatic accessible name, so `select-name` (which fires only when *no* name exists) does not trigger. However, the `title`-only labelling is flagged under **`label-title-only`** (see §4).

