## 5. `label-title-only` violations — Scorer only

| Element | CSS selector | Title text (current label source) |
|---------|-------------|----------------------------------|
| `<input id="student-name">` | `#student-name` | "The full name of the student…" |
| `<input id="student-id">` | `#student-id` | "The student's institutional ID…" |
| `<input id="student-tutor">` | `#student-tutor` | "Your name or initials…" |
| `<input id="student-date">` | `#student-date` | "Auto-filled with today's date…" |
| `<select id="late-penalty-select">` | `#late-penalty-select` | "Apply a deduction if the student…" |

Root cause: visible `<label>` elements are not programmatically associated (missing `for` attribute); screen readers fall back to `title`, which is non-discoverable by most users and unreachable on mobile.

