## 6. WCAG-grounded fix recommendations

| Rule | Fix |
|------|-----|
| **color-contrast** — `text-slate-400` everywhere | Replace `text-slate-400` (#94a3b8, ≈2.8:1) with `text-slate-600` (#475569, ≈5.9:1) for all body/label/hint text; reserve slate-400 only for decorative or disabled states. *[WCAG 1.4.3 — AA requires 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large/bold ≥18.67px/bold]* |
| **color-contrast** — `.bg-emerald-600` CTA button | Darken to `bg-emerald-700` (#047857, ≈5.2:1 on white) or use `text-white`+`font-bold` with emerald-700. *[WCAG 1.4.3]* |
| **color-contrast** — `.btn-blue` / `.btn-green` | Verify button bg colours meet 3:1 against white text (large text rule applies if ≥18px bold); adjust to darker shade if below. *[WCAG 1.4.3]* |
| **color-contrast** — `.text-amber-600` builder hint | Change to `text-amber-700` (#b45309, ≈4.7:1 on white). *[WCAG 1.4.3]* |
| **color-contrast** — sub-10px/11px hint text | Either increase font size to ≥14px (so 3:1 applies instead of 4.5:1) or switch colour to slate-600+. *[WCAG 1.4.3 — 3:1 threshold for ≥18pt/14pt bold only]* |
| **color-contrast** — `.site-footer__muted` / footer headings | Raise to at least slate-600 equivalent in the footer stylesheet. *[WCAG 1.4.3]* |
| **link-in-text-block** — Ko-fi link in footer | Add `text-decoration: underline` (always, not just on hover) so the link is visually distinct without relying on colour. *[WCAG 1.4.1 — Use of Colour]* |
| **label-title-only** — Student Name / ID / Tutor / Date / Late Penalty | Add `for="<input-id>"` to each `<label>` element (e.g. `<label for="student-name">`), removing the sole reliance on `title`. *[WCAG 4.1.2 — Name, Role, Value; SC 1.3.1]* |
| **region** — orphaned content in Builder + Scorer | Wrap the sticky-header/nav-rail in `<header>` or `role="banner"`, wrap the scoring workspace in `<main>`, and wrap the onboarding banner in `<aside>` or `role="complementary"`; ensure `<h1 class="sr-only">` is inside `<main>`. *[WCAG 1.3.1 / ARIA Landmark Roles]* |
